50|$|<b>Contractual</b> <b>capacity</b> {{refers to}} the ability of a party to enter into a legally binding contract. Minors, drunks, and the mentally {{impaired}} may not possess adequate capacity however the ordinary reasonable person is presumed by default to have <b>contractual</b> <b>capacity.</b> Where {{there is a lack of}} capacity to contract, an agreement may be rendered void.|$|E
