5000|$|All persons, whether {{natural or}} juristic, have passive legal {{capacity}} and can therefore bear rights and duties, but not all have <b>contractual</b> <b>capacity,</b> which enables persons to conclude the contracts by which those rights and duties are conferred. Natural persons {{can be divided into}} three groups: ...|$|E
50|$|The {{history of}} the prepay mobile phone began in the 1990s when mobile phone {{operators}} sought to expand their market reach. Up until this point, mobile phone services were exclusively offered on a postpaid basis (contract-based), which excluded individuals with poor credit ratings and minors {{under the age of}} 18 (the typical age of <b>contractual</b> <b>capacity).</b>|$|E
